'''Chof Beis Shvat''', the 22nd day of the month of [[Shvat]] in the [[Hebrew calendar]] ({{lang-he|'''כ״ב שבט'''}}) is the [[yartzeit]] of Rebbetzin [[Chaya Mushka Schneerson]], the wife of the seventh [[Rebbe]] of the [[Chabad]] [[Hasidic]] movement. The day is marked by the Chabad community with public gatherings and other commemorations.<ref>[http://www.chabadinfo.com/?url=newsnew_en&string=tag_Chof%20Beis%20Shvat ''Chabad.info'']. Accessed April 27, 2014.</ref>

==History==
[[File:Chaya Mushka Schneerson grave.jpg|thumb|200px|right|Rebbitzin Chaya Mushka Schneerson's gravesite visited each year on the 22nd of Shvat]]
[[Chaya Mushka Schneerson]], the wife of Rabbi [[Menachem Mendel Schneerson]], the seventh [[Rebbe]] of the [[Chabad]] [[Hasidic]] movement, died on the Hebrew day of 22nd of Shvat, 5788 (February 10, 1988). Chaya Mushka is known in the Chabad community as "the Rebbetzin".<ref>Marcus, Shmuel. [http://www.chabad.org/library/article_cdo/aid/110756/jewish/Her-Passing.htm "Her passing."] ''Chabad.org''. Accessed April 27, 2014.</ref><ref>Zaklikowsky. David. [http://www.crownheights.info/chabad-news/370788/chof-beis-shvat-yohrtziet-of-rebbetzen-chaya-mushka/ "Chof Beis Shvat."] ''crownheights.info''. Accessed April 27, 2014.</ref>

The anniversary of her death, or "[[yartzeit]]", is marked each year by the Chabad community by public gatherings, or "[[farbrengens]]".<ref>[http://www.chabadinfo.com/index.php?url=article_en&id=26150 "Thousands of Women Gather at Central Farbrengen."] ''Chabadinfo.com''. February 16, 2012. Accessed April 27, 2014.</ref> The day is also marked by a number of Chabad girls and women's conventions.<ref>[http://www.crownheights.info/general/10276/19th-annual-chof-bais-shvat-bais-rivkah-high-schools-convention/ "19th Annual Beis Rivka Convention."] ''crownheights.info''. Accessed April 27, 2014.</ref>

===Ohel visits===
Many Chabad Hasidim visit the grave of Rebbetzin Chaya Mushka on the 22nd of Shvat. Visitors accompany the visit by praying at the grave of Rabbi [[Menachem Mendel Schneerson]] at [[Ohel Chabad-Lubavitch]].<ref>[http://www.crownheights.info/photo-galleries/422773/kinus-hashluchos-prayers-at-the-ohel/ "Kinus Hashluchos Pray at the Ohel."] ''crownheights.info''. Accessed April 27, 2014.</ref>

===Kinus Hashluchos===
The most popular event held in honor of the 22nd of Shvat is the Kinus Hashluchos, the annual convention of the women [[Shaliach (Chabad)|Shluchos]], or Chabad emissaries.<ref>Mauer, Naomi Klass.[http://www.jewishpress.com/sections/features/feautures-on-jewish-world/a-magnificent-weekend-with-the-chabad-shluchos/2014/02/21/ "A Magnificent Weekend With The Chabad Shluchos."] ''The Jewish Press''. February 21, 2014. Accessed April 27, 2014.</ref><ref>[http://www.collive.com/show_news.rtx?id=28791 "Kinus Hashluchos Gala Banquent."] ''COLlive.com''. Accessed April 27, 2014.</ref>

